Minimal shielded pool — a BN254 / Groth16 shielded pool for Ethereum

Original sources (the spend circuit, the Python reference and generators, the
pool contract, the wallet, and the devnet tooling) are licensed under
Apache-2.0 (see LICENSE).

This project builds on:

  iden3/circomlib 2.0.5 and iden3/circomlibjs 0.1.7 (GPL-3.0): the spend
  circuit includes circomlib's poseidon.circom at compile time (fetched via
  npm, not vendored), and reference/poseidon_bn254_constants.json plus
  vectors/poseidon_bn254_vectors.json are exported from circomlibjs by
  tooling/export_vectors.js. contracts/src/PoseidonBN254.sol and the split
  PoseidonT3.sol / PoseidonT4.sol are generated from those constants.

  iden3/snarkjs 0.7.5 (GPL-3.0): contracts/src/Groth16Verifier.sol is generated
  by snarkjs's `zkey export solidityverifier` and carries its GPL-3.0 header;
  it is the standard snarkjs verifier template instantiated with this circuit's
  verification key.

devnet/frametx.py is vendored from lambdaclass/ethrex
(scripts/hegota-devnet/frametx.py, hegota-devnet branch), the reference
type-0x06 frame-transaction encoder for the Hegotá devnet, with a one-line
type-annotation widening for Python 3.9. ethrex is Apache-2.0 / MIT
dual-licensed. devnet/pool_frametx.py and REVIEW.md are original Apache-2.0
work.
